00:00:00.290 --> 00:00:02.180
As a quick quiz, which of the

00:00:02.180 --> 00:00:06.040
following make the internet's design fundamentally insecure?

00:00:06.040 --> 00:00:10.780
The On by default nature of the design, the fact that IP Addresses might be

00:00:10.780 --> 00:00:15.500
easy for an attacker to guess, that attacks can look like normal traffic, and

00:00:15.500 --> 00:00:18.120
that the internet is actually a federation

00:00:18.120 --> 00:00:20.710
of tens of thousands of independently operated networks?

